{{head|fr|article|g=m|feminine|la|masculine and feminine plural|les|prevocalic masculine or feminine singular|l'}}

# [[the]] (definite article)
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Le''' lait du matin.|'''The''' milk of the morning.}}
# {{n-g|Used before abstract nouns; not translated in English.}}
#: {{ux|fr|'''L''''amour est aveugle.|[[love is blind|Love is blind.]]}}
# {{n-g|Used before the names of most countries, many subnational regions, and other geographical names including names of lakes and streets; not translated into English in most cases.}}
#: {{ux|fr|Je vais visiter '''le''' Canada l'année prochaine, surtout '''l''''Ontario et '''le''' Québec.|I will be visiting Canada next year, especially Ontario and Quebec.}}
#: {{ux|fr|'''La''' place Rouge se trouve au cœur de Moscou.|Red Square is located in the heart of Moscow.}}
# (''before parts of the body'') [[the]]; [[my]], [[your]], ''etc.''
#: {{uxi|fr|Il s’est cassé '''la''' jambe.|He has broken '''his''' leg.}}
# (''before units'') [[a]], [[an]], [[per]]
#: {{uxi|fr|cinquante kilomètres à '''l’'''heure|fifty kilometres an hour}}
#: {{uxi|fr|trois dollars '''le''' morceau|three dollars '''per''' piece}}
# (''before dates'') [[on]]
#: {{uxi|fr|Je suis née '''le''' 1er juillet 1967.|I was born '''on''' July 1, 1967.}}

====Usage notes====
* '''le''' becomes '''l’''' before a vowel or an unaspirated h.
*: {{uxi|fr|'''l’'''amour|t=love}}
*: {{uxi|fr|'''l’'''endroit|t=the place}}
*: {{uxi|fr|'''l’'''homme|t=the man}}
* When the article '''le''' is preceded by the prepositions {{m|fr|de}} or {{m|fr|à}}, ''*de le'' or ''*à le'' is not used (except dialectally); instead, it is contracted into {{m|fr|du}} or {{m|fr|au}}, respectively. Likewise, ''*de les'' and ''*à les'' are replaced by {{m|fr|des}} and {{m|fr|aux}} (except dialectally). However, '''la''' may be preceded by ''de'' and ''à''.
*: {{uxi|fr|Il a une cicatrice '''au''' visage.|t=He has a scar on the face. / He has a scar on his face.}}
* ''*de le'' and ''*à le'' become '''de l'''' and '''à l'''' respectively in front of a vowel or an unaspirated h.

{{head|fr|pronoun form|cat2=personal pronouns|g=m|feminine|la|masculine and feminine plural|les}}

# {{qualifier|direct object}} [[him]], [[it]]
#: {{ux|fr|Où est Malik ? Je ne '''le''' vois pas.|Where is Malik? I don't see '''him'''.}}
#: {{ux|fr|Mon sac ? Je vais '''le''' mettre dans la voiture.|My bag? I'm going to put '''it''' in the car.}}
# {{n-g|used to refer to something previously mentioned or implied; not translated in English}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Je suis petit et lui, il '''l’'''est aussi.|t=I am small and he is too|lit=... and he is it too}}

====Usage notes====
* Unlike the definite article '''le''', the pronouns '''le''' and '''les''' may be preceded by the prepositions ''de'' and ''à'': {{uxi|fr|Je cherchais '''à le''' voir.|I was trying '''to''' see '''him'''.}}

